commit: a4fd62d7 + autovec additions (uncommitted at run time)
host:   AMD Ryzen 9 7950X (Zen 4)
cmd:    cargo bench --bench deinterleave --features experimental
zenbench: 0.1.7
date:   2026-04-29 UTC
notes:
  - Added third bench column "scalar+autovec(avx2)": same scalar source as
    `scalar`, but compiled inside an #[arcane] AVX2 target_feature region so
    LLVM is free to autovectorize. Lets us separate "what does LLVM do for
    free under AVX2" from "what does the hand-written shuffle pattern add
    on top".
  - Naive `scalar` numbers came out slower in this run vs the prior log
    (e.g. 256px L1: 182ns → 284ns); zenbench interleaves all three columns
    per round so cache pressure is higher with 3 variants. Within-run
    ratios are what matter.
  - As before, "iB/s" column appears miscalibrated; trust the ns timings.
